events.name: Kandace Springs
events.info: While 2018 Indigo LP found the Nashville singer pianist using modern production to bend sound into new genre forms in collaboration with Karriem Riggins, this set adheres sonically to jazz while Springs travels back and forth across a near century of music. While the feel is as rich and complex as our hosts voice, the concept is simple. Springs covers the women who inspired her while she was growing up, putting her own spin on songs associated with a dozen of the greatest female vocalists of all time, Ella Fitzgerald, Roberta Flack, Astrud Gilberto, Lauryn Hill, Billie Holiday, Norah Jones, Diana Krall, Carmen McRae, Bonnie Raitt, Sade, Nina Simone, and Dusty Springfield. This is an album I have been wanting to make forever, says Springs. It really expresses my love for all of these singers and gratitude for what they gave me. Each taught me something different and all of those lessons combined to make me who I am now.

events.info: The Up Close and Personal with the PSO @ Jimmy's Chamber Music Series explores the borderlands between jazz and classical music.. Each performance will feature ensembles of Portsmouth Symphony musicians who will showcase the richness, flexibility, and often surprising range of the classical chamber music repertoire in Jimmy's century-old, spectacularly restored, state-of-the-art club. The winter blues have never sounded more beautiful. Gershwin's "Rhapsody in Blue," arranged for piano quartet, blends jazz and classical music and is the centerpiece of this concert. events.name: The Other Favorites "Unamericana" Tour
events.info: The Other Favorites are an indie folk duo based in Brooklyn, New York, that consists of Joshua Lee Turner and Carson McKee. They are perhaps best known for their performances on YouTube, which have garnered millions of views. A shared love of traditional bluegrass, folk, and classic rock music underpins their songwriting, which is distinguished by virtuosic guitar work, incisive lyricism, and tight vocal harmony. Their new album, Unamericana, explores a complicated relationship with the American identity. After meeting at their 8th grade talent show, Turner and McKee began performing together in their former hometown of Charlotte, North Carolina. They self-released their first full-length album, Novelty, in 2011, followed by Naysayer in 2018, and Live in London in 2019. Unamericana will be released on November 19th, 2021.

events.info: The Up Close and Personal with the PSO @ Jimmy's Chamber Music Series explores the borderlands between jazz and classical music. Paired with fine food including appetizer, dinner and dessert, this six-concert series promises chamber music like you've never experienced it before. events.name: Life In Full Color
events.info: The Cambridge Symphony Orchestra returns to the stage with a program that will bring vibrancy and color back into your life after the grayness of the pandemic. Su Lian Tans Langkawi (2021), an expansion of her earlier Langkawi Fanfare (2015), opens the program with sonic depictions of the myths and legends of Malaysia (specially, Langkawi Island, off the coast), the composers original home. Originally performed by the Ballets Russes in the early 20th century, two colorful suites from Manuel de Fallas ballet The Three Cornered Hat feature Spanish rhythms and dances that evoke the antics of a magistrate infatuated with a millers wife. Finally, Aaron Coplands Appalachian Spring portrays a celebratory occasion among rural people in Pennsylvania in the 19th century; originally commissioned as a ballet score by the choreographer Martha Graham, the orchestral suite evokes an agrarian landscape with an animated, iconic American sound.
